==English==

===Pronunciation===
gō'nə-ŏs'kə-pē

===Noun===
'''gonioscopy'''

# The use of a goniolens (also known as a gonioscope) in conjunction with a slit lamp or operating microscope to gain a view of the anatomical angle formed between the eye's [[cornea]] and [[iris]], known as the iridocorneal angle.